<item>
            <title>[AMQ-6124] failover backup transports do not update the brokerInfo leaving stale org.apache.activemq.ActiveMQConnection#getBrokerName</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6124</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;with broker url &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;failover:(tcp:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//a:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;,tcp://b:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt; &quot;)?randomize=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&amp;amp;priorityBackup=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The brokerName as reported by &lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.activemq.ActiveMQConnection#getBrokerName stays at A even after failover to B.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The backup transport are started up front and the brokerInfo is not cached so it  never gets replayed to the jms connection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same is true for the backup attribute&lt;/p&gt;</description>
